  <text>
    <body>
      <div type="edition" xml:lang="la" xml:space="preserve">
        <ab>
          <lb n="1"/><expan><abbr>I</abbr></expan> <expan><abbr>O</abbr></expan> <expan><abbr>M</abbr></expan>
          <lb n="2"/>Aurelius
          <lb n="3"/>Victor
          <lb n="4"/><expan><abbr>v</abbr><ex>otum</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>s</abbr><ex>olvit</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>l</abbr><ex>ibens</ex></expan>
          <lb n="5"/><expan><abbr>m</abbr><ex>erito</ex></expan>
        </ab>
      </div>
      <div type="translation" xml:lang="en">
        <p>To Jupiter Best and Greatest. Aurelius Victor willingly and deservedly fulfilled his vow.</p>
      </div>
      <div type="commentary">
        <p>The dedication formula v(otum) s(olvit) l(ibens) m(erito) is among the commonest on Roman votive altars.</p>
      </div>
